@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Kia Sonet vs Tata Nexon (2025) – Which Subcompact SUV Wins?";
}
@section MetaTags {
    <meta name="keywords" content=" BikeCarHub, Kia Sonet vs Tata Nexon, Sonet vs Tata Nexon 2025, best compact SUV India, Kia Sonet review, Tata Nexon features, Sonet vs Tata Nexon mileage, Sonet vs Tata Nexon safety, Sonet vs Tata Nexon price" />
    <meta name="description" content="BikeCarHub-Compare Kia Sonet vs Tata Nexon  for performance, safety, features, and value. Find out which 2025 compact SUV suits your needs with our detailed comparison." />
}

@functions {
    public string Truncate(string input, int length)
    {
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(input) || input.Length <= length)
            return input;
        return input.Substring(0, length) + "...";
    }
}
<body id="bg">
    @* <div class="header-img"><img src="~/images/main-slider/header.png" alt="bikecarhubheaderimage" title="bikecarhubheaderimage" /></div> *@
    <div class="m-t90">
        <div><h1 class="latest-bike-head">@Model.BlogHeading</h1></div>
        <div class=" latest-bike-container">
            @* <div style="background-image:url(@ViewBag.TWNews.ImageURL);background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position: center;background-size:contain ;height: 400px;box-shadow: 5px 10px 8px #888888;border-radius:10px;background-color:#ebecee;padding:60px;"></div> *@
            <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-image">
                <img src="@Model.ImageURL" alt="@Model.BlogHeading" title="@Model.BlogHeading" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='@Url.Content("~/images/default.jpg")';" />
                <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-text">
                    <p><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> @Model.Date?.ToString("d MMM yyyy")</p>
                    @* <p>@ViewBag.TWNews.NewsSummary</p> *@
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="latest-bikes-details-content">

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Written by:</span> BikeCarHub Editorial Team</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Published on:</span> 27th June 2025</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Introduction</h2>

                <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.BlogSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <p>Let's explore this head-to-head comparison based on design, features, performance, safety, variants, and pricing to help you decide which one is best for you.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Design & Styling</h2>
                <h3 class="subheading">Kia Sonet 2025</h3>
               
                <p>The 2025 Kia Sonet sports a refreshed look with updated <span class="font-weight-700">LED headlamps</span>, revised <span class="font-weight-700">tiger-nose grille</span>, and more aggressive bumpers. The <span class="font-weight-700">X-Line variant</span> adds dark chrome elements and a unique matte exterior. The Sonet retains a youthful, premium vibe, especially in its <span class="font-weight-700">GT Line</span> and <span class="font-weight-700">X-Line trims</span>.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Tata Nexon 2025</h3>
                
                <p>Tata Nexon received a major facelift in late 2023, which carries into the 2025 model year. It features a bold <span class="font-weight-700">split LED headlight design</span>, <span class="font-weight-700">connected LED tail lamp</span>, and a wider, more sculpted stance. It offers a sportier, muscular look with high road presence.</p>

                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Dimension</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Kia Sonet</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Tata Nexon</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Length</td>
                                <td>3995 mm</td>
                                <td>3995 mm</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Width</td>
                                <td>1790 mm</td>
                                <td>1804 mm</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Height</td>
                                <td>1610 mm</td>
                                <td>1620 mm</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Wheelbase</td>
                                <td>2500 mm</td>
                                <td>2498 mm</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Verdict</span>: The Nexon has a bolder, muscular design while the Sonet feels more premium and urban-focused. Both excel in design but cater to slightly different tastes.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Powertrain & Performance</h2>
                <h3 class="subheading">Kia Sonet (2025) Engine Options:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.2L Petrol</span> (83 PS / 115 Nm) — 5-speed MT</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.0L Turbo Petrol</span> (120 PS / 172 Nm) — iMT & 7DCT</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.5L Diesel</span> (116 PS / 250 Nm) — 6MT / 6AT</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Tata Nexon (2025) Engine Options:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.2L Turbo Petrol</span> (120 PS / 170 Nm) — 5MT, 6MT, 6AMT, 7DCA</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.5L Diesel</span> (115 PS / 260 Nm) — 6MT, 6AMT</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Both also offer <span class="font-weight-700">multiple drive modes</span>, but the Nexon has an edge with a smoother <span class="font-weight-700">dual-clutch automatic (DCA)</span> for petrol.</p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Verdict</span>: Nexon offers more transmission options and a refined turbo-petrol-DCA combo, while Sonet provides excellent diesel-automatic performance.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Features Comparison</h2>
                <h3 class="subheading">Kia Sonet Key Features (Top GTX+ / X-Line):</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>10.25" touchscreen infotainment</li>
                    <li>Bose 7-speaker system</li>
                    <li>360° camera</li>
                    <li>Ventilated front seats</li>
                    <li>Digital cluster with navigation</li>
                    <li>ADAS (Advanced Driver Assistance System)</li>
                    <li>Front parking sensors</li>
                    <li>Air purifier with virus protection</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Tata Nexon Key Features (Top Fearless+ S):</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>10.25" touchscreen with wireless Android Auto/Apple CarPlay</li>
                    <li>10.25" digital cluster</li>
                    <li>360° camera</li>
                    <li>JBL sound system</li>
                    <li>Ventilated seats</li>
                    <li>Sunroof</li>
                    <li>Air purifier</li>
                    <li>Arcade.ev app suite</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Verdict</span>: Feature-wise, it's a close call. Sonet scores with Bose audio and ADAS, while Nexon has a cleaner UI, better display integration, and digital cockpit feel.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Safety Features</h2>
                <h3 class="subheading">Kia Sonet Safety:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>6 airbags standard across variants</li>
                    <li>ESC, VSM, Hill Assist</li>
                    <li>ADAS (GTX+ and X-Line only): Forward Collision Warning, Lane Keep Assist, High Beam Assist, Driver Attention Alert</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Tata Nexon Safety:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>6 airbags standard</li>
                    <li>ESP, Roll-over Mitigation, TPMS</li>
                    <li>360° camera with dynamic guidelines</li>
                    <li>Emergency call and breakdown call</li>
                    <li>ISOFIX child anchors</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Crash Rating</span>:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Previous-gen Nexon: 5-Star Global NCAP</li>
                    <li>Sonet (new gen not yet tested under GNCAP 2024 protocol)</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Verdict</span>: Nexon has proven GNCAP safety credentials. Sonet gets ADAS, which is rare in this segment. It's a safety vs tech debate.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Pricing & Variants</h2>
                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Model</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Base Price (₹)</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Top Variant (₹)</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Top Features Include</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Kia Sonet</td>
                                <td>₹7.99 L</td>
                                <td>₹14.74 L</td>
                                <td>ADAS, ventilated seats, 360° cam, Bose, sunroof</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Tata Nexon</td>
                                <td>₹8.00 L</td>
                                <td>₹14.50 L</td>
                                <td>JBL, 360° cam, digital cockpit, air purifier, sunroof</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Verdict</span>: Prices are nearly identical across the range. Sonet offers more trims, while Nexon trims are simpler to understand and better spaced.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Fuel Efficiency</h2>
                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Powertrain</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Kia Sonet (ARAI)</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Tata Nexon (ARAI)</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>1.2L Petrol MT</td>
                                <td>18.4 kmpl</td>
                                <td>---</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>1.0L Turbo Petrol DCT</td>
                                <td>19.2 kmpl</td>
                                <td>17.4 kmpl (DCA)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>1.5L Diesel MT/AT</td>
                                <td>24.1 / 19.0 kmpl</td>
                                <td>23.2 / 24.0 kmpl</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Verdict</span>: Sonet diesel MT is the most efficient; Nexon diesel AMT leads in city mileage.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">After-sales & Warranty</h2>
                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Brand</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Warranty</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Service Network</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Kia</td>
                                <td>3 yrs / 1 lakh km (5 yrs optional)</td>
                                <td>Growing rapidly</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Tata</td>
                                <td>3 yrs / 1 lakh km (upgradable)</td>
                                <td>Wider rural reach</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p>Kia's service experience is more premium, while Tata has improved reliability and lower running costs.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Final Verdict — Which One to Choose?</h2>
                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Priority</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Winner</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Reason</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Best for diesel commuters</td>
                                <td>Sonet</td>
                                <td>Refined diesel AT + better mileage</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Best petrol automatic</td>
                                <td>Nexon</td>
                                <td>Smoother 7-speed DCA + more drive modes</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Feature-loaded experience</td>
                                <td>Tie</td>
                                <td>Both have 360° cam, ventilated seats, wireless features</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>ADAS Technology</td>
                                <td>Sonet</td>
                                <td>Only one in segment offering ADAS</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Proven safety + crash rating</td>
                                <td>Nexon</td>
                                <td>5-star rated platform, more robust body design</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Interior experience</td>
                                <td>Nexon</td>
                                <td>Full-digital cockpit, connected feel</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>After-sales service</td>
                                <td>Kia</td>
                                <td>Premium touch, fast-growing dealership network</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Conclusion</h2>
                <p>If you're seeking <span class="font-weight-700">premium design, top-end diesel refinement, or ADAS</span>, go for the <span class="font-weight-700">Kia Sonet</span>. But if you value <span class="font-weight-700">proven safety, punchy petrol DCA, and a futuristic interior</span>, the <span class="font-weight-700">Tata Nexon</span> is a more compelling buy in 2025.</p>
                <p>Both are excellent SUVs—choose the one that fits your lifestyle, location, and driving needs best.</p>

